=== Noun ===

'''pidgin''' 
#A combination of two languages with a simple grammar and vocabulary, used to facilitate communication between speakers of two different languages.  A pidgin has no (or very few) native speakers; when a pidgin acquires a native speaker community, it often becomes a [[creole]].

